Mathematical Audit Notebook
Kirr-Knox (2026): Multi-Peak Ground States of the NLS
This notebook systematically verifies every mathematical claim, derivation, and computation in the research report. Each section corresponds to a section of the paper
1. Setup and Core Definitions
Define all fundamental quantities used throughout the paper.
In[1]:= ClearAll["<Global`*>"];

(* Equilateral triangle geometry*)
{a,h}={1/2,1/\[Sqrt]3};

(* Verify equilateral constraint: all side lengths = 1 *)
Print["Equilateral check: 2a = ", 2a, " (should be 1)"];
Print["Side length check: a^2 + (3h/2)^2 = ", Simplify[a^2+(3h/2)^2], " (should be 1)"];

(* Peak positions (canonical orientation) *)
{y1,y2,y3}={{0,h},{-a,-h/2},{a,-h/2}};

(* Hessian (diagonal) *)
Hv=DiagonalMatrix[{\[Lambda]1,\[Lambda]2}];

(* Verify all pairwise distances *)
Print["|y1-y2| = ", Simplify[Norm[y1-y2]]];
Print["|y1-y3| = ", Simplify[Norm[y1-y3]]];
Print["|y2-y3| = ", Simplify[Norm[y2-y3]]];
